OL,6,FShe added: "An independent public
OL,7,Finvestigation dealing with the
OL,8,Fcoroner's concerns, capable of dealing
OL,9,Fwith sensitive material, with the
OL,10,FBrown family legally represented,
OL,11,Fprovided with the relevant material
OL,12,Fand able to examine the principal
OL,13,Fwitnesses must be held without further
OL,14,Fdelay in order to satisfy the
OL,15,Fobligations imposed by Article 2 of
OL,16,Fthe European Convention on Human
OL,17,FRights, which all parties agree the UK
OL,18,FGovernment is in breach of."
