OL,6,FPreliminary inquest proceedings had
OL,7,Falready heard that in excess of 25
OL,8,Fpeople had been linked by intelligence
OL,9,Fto the murder, including several state
OL,10,Fagents.
OL,12,FIt had also been alleged in court that
OL,13,Fsurveillance of a suspect in the
OL,14,Fmurder was temporarily stopped on the
OL,15,Fevening of the killing, only to resume
OL,16,Fagain the following morning.
OL,18,FCoroner Mr Justice Kinney called on
OL,19,Fthe Government to establish a public
OL,20,Finquiry into the loyalist murder.
